---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Bio — Bradley Davis"
  current="bio"
  description="Senior backend engineer turned AI-native builder — MCP servers, agentic engineering, and the path that got him there."
>
  <div class="hero">
    <picture>
      <source
        type="image/webp"
        srcset="/images/headshot-88.webp 1x, /images/headshot-176.webp 2x, /images/headshot-264.webp 3x"
      />
      <img
        class="headshot"
        src="/images/headshot-176.jpg"
        width="88"
        height="88"
        alt=""
      />
    </picture>
    <h1>Bradley Davis</h1>
  </div>

  <p class="lede">
    Senior backend engineer turned AI-native builder. Seven years shipping
    production payment and platform systems before pivoting into agentic
    engineering full time.
  </p>

  <p>
    I left OKX in May 2026 and went all-in on agentic engineering: MCP
    servers, multi-agent orchestration, LLM-app architecture, the patterns
    that hold up outside a demo. I run all of it off a five-machine,
    Nix-managed homelab (Caddy reverse proxy, self-hosted git, Pi-hole DNS,
    Home Assistant, ZFS-replicated storage) that doubles as a daily proving
    ground for whatever I'm building right now.
  </p>

  <p>
    I got here sideways, and it set a pattern I still run on: go to where
    the problem actually lives, get hands-on, own it end to end. Before
    software, that meant a year supervising measurement-while-drilling
    operations on Wyoming oil rigs, then writing coreboot and UEFI firmware
    for embedded x86 boards, then an HPC internship at Cray. A master's in
    computer science at UW-Madison turned that into a real engineering
    career: three years on webhooks infrastructure at Intuit (10-20M
    notifications a day at 99.9% reliability), then four years on OKX's
    fiat payments platform (30+ payment providers across APAC, EU, and the
    US), where I led the platform's largest architectural effort. Something
    like a forward-deployed engineer before the term existed.
  </p>

  <p>
    Off the keyboard: an Eagle Scout who once saved a life with CPR, a
    former ski instructor, and two small kids.
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
    Full history on the <a href="/resume">resume</a>. Reach me at
    <a href="mailto:hire@bdavis.ai">hire@bdavis.ai</a>.
  </p>
</Base>
